==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: egg-plant
<hw>egg-plant</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant (<spn>Solanum
Melongena</spn>), of East Indian origin, allied to the tomato, and
bearing a large, glossy, edible fruit, shaped somewhat like an egg;
mad-apple. It is widely cultivated for its fruit, commonly eaten as a
vegetable.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> eggplant, aubergine, brinjal, eggplant bush, garden
egg, mad apple, <spn>Solanum melongena</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The fruit of the <er>eggplant{1}</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>egg-producing</ent>⟦br⟧
